    "causal_summary": "The 005 post-remediation verification (2026-04-26 18:49) showed that the Cluster 1 truncation fix is NOT live in the daemon: `memory_context({input:\"Semantic Search\"})` still returns `meta.tokenBudgetEnforcement.{enforced:true, truncated:true, returnedResultCount:3, originalResultCount:5}` while `actualTokens=65 / budgetTokens=3500` (1.9% utilization) and `data.content[0].text` still contains `{\"count\":0,\"results\":[]}`. The 007 research isolated the root cause as soft contracts: `actualTokens` is reported AFTER fallback (post-enforcement size), there is no `preEnforcementTokens` to distinguish overflow from returned size, and the wrapper has no payload/count invariant assertion that the metadata's `returnedResultCount` matches the actual `JSON.parse(content[0].text).data.results.length`.",
